  "texts": [
    "As shown in Figure 2, our model architecture consists of three parts: Representation Encoder, Edge Predictor, and Level Predictor.",
    "Accepting one sentence, noised blocks (with timestep t) as inputs, the model network f θ generates the predicted blocks ẑ0 appropriately.",
    "Given an input sentence S = {x 1, x 2,..., x L } composed of L words or indexes, here our sentence en- coder consists of a pre-trained BERT (Devlin et al., 2019) and a bi-directional LSTM (Lample et al., 2016).",
    "Utilizing our encoder, token embeddings along with positional embeddings as the input are transformed into contextualized sentence representation R H ∈ R L×d.",
    "Then the inner span tokens are extracted from the word indexes indicated by the edges of our blocks, yielding the edge representation R E ∈ R N ×d following mean-pooling."
  ],
